A Makueni police officer killed his colleague and injured two others at their station on Wednesday night. Area police boss Bosita Omukolongolo said the shooter fled with his gun. "The officer is at large but we are looking for him. We are yet to know why he shot his colleagues," he told the media at his office. One of the survivors was shot in the shoulder and the other in the thigh.Â They were taken Makueni Level Four Hospital. The officer shot in the thigh was later transferred to Armed Forces Memorial Hospital along Mbgathi Road in Nairobi. Makueni senior medical superintendent Emmanuel Laiposha said he needed specialised treatment. Click here for the latest political news